        "exhibitionLabelText": {
            "en": {
                "purposes": [
                    "Sigg Online"
                ],
                "labels": [
                    {
                        "purpose": "Sigg Online",
                        "text": "Though this seemingly empty canvas evokes elements of abstraction and minimalism, it draws from the Taoist concept of ‘nothingness’ rather than Western art history. There is a meditative quality to Qiu’s practice. In Untitled  (No. 30), spectators need to be patient before a figurative landscape – replete with drifting clouds, trees, and riverbanks – appears behind the veil of white. Qiu trained in traditional landscape ink painting, but after a visit to France in the 1980s, he developed a disciplined approach that fuses elements of Impressionism and Taoism to create canvases that drift between the conventions of Western scenery and Chinese landscapes."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "zh-hant": {
                "purposes": [
                    "Sigg Online"
                ],
                "labels": [
                    {
                        "purpose": "Sigg Online",
                        "text": "這幅看似空白的油畫，雖然令人聯想到抽象和簡約主義，但其實非以西方藝術史為基礎，而是道家的「虛白」。邱世華的藝術實踐具有冥想特質。觀賞《無題（第30號）》時必須耐心靜候，在虛無之間慢慢發現浮雲、樹木和河岸，形成一幅具象風景畫。邱氏本來研習傳統山水畫，1980年代到訪法國後，隨之發展出一套揉合印象主義與道家思想的作畫方式，一系列油彩作品遊走西方傳統風景畫與中國山水畫之間。"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    },
